  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive legal framework under Bank Secrecy Act\n- Strong emphasis on financial institution reporting requirements\n- Aggressive prosecution with substantial criminal penalties\n- Extraterritorial reach of anti-money laundering (AML) regulations\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified regulatory approach through Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Centralized reporting and information-sharing mechanisms\n- Risk-based compliance standards\n- Strong focus on financial transparency\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Sophisticated legal framework\n- Advanced technological monitoring systems\n- Strict customer due diligence requirements\n- Significant regulatory penalties\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Historically more lenient banking secrecy laws\n- Recent reforms increasing transparency\n- Strong international cooperation mechanisms\n- Sophisticated financial compliance systems\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Strict governmental oversight\n- Increasing international compliance standards\n- Focus on preventing capital flight\n\n6. Singapore\n- Rigorous regulatory environment\n- Advanced technological monitoring\n- Strong international cooperation\n- Significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n7. Russia\n- Less transparent regulatory framework\n- Inconsistent enforcement mechanisms\n- Emerging compliance infrastructure\n\nEach jurisdiction demonstrates unique approaches balancing financial privacy, economic interests, and regulatory effectiveness.",
